\DOC Theory

\TYPE {Theory : (string -> searchpath)}

\SYNOPSIS
Generates a {searchpath} that consists precisely of the named theory segment.

\LIBRARY trs

\DESCRIBE
A {searchpath} is either a single theory segment, or it is a hierarchy of
theory segments. {Theory} is used to generate a {searchpath} of the first
kind. A search path is, as its name suggests, a specification of where a
search for theorems should take place.

\FAILURE
Never fails.

\SEEALSO
Ancestors, ancestors_excluding, Ancestry.

\ENDDOC
